==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wind signal
<hw>Wind signal</hw>. <def>In general, any signal announcing information
concerning winds, and esp. the expected approach of winds whose
direction and force are dangerous to shipping, etc. The wind-signal
system of the United States Weather Bureau consists of <xex>storm</xex>,
<xex>information</xex>, <xex>hurricane</xex>, <xex>hot wind</xex>, and
<xex>inland storm signals</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Windsor</ent>⟦br⟧
